{"title_page": "Saint Francis of Assisi College", "text_new": "{{COI|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox university\n| name = Saint Francis of Assisi College\n| native_name = Kolehiyo ng San Francisco de Assisi\n| image_name = SFACS-Logo.png\n| image_size = 175px\n| image_alt = \n| caption = Educating with Respect, Cultivating an Atmosphere of Understanding\n| latin_name = \n| former_names = Saint Francis of Assisi College System\n| motto = ''Fides Et Humilitas'' {{small|(Latin)}}\n| mottoeng = ''Faith And Humility''<br>\nTagline      : '''Academics'''. ''And beyond.''\n| type = [[Private school|Private]], [[Roman Catholic]] [[Research]] [[Coeducation]]al Basic and Higher education institution\n| established = 1981\n| founders = {{small|Dr. Evangeline O\u00f1as-Orosco}}<br>{{small|Dr. Arturo Agapito Orosco, Sr.}}\n| closed = \n| affiliation = \n| endowment = \n| budget = \n| officer_in_charge = \n| chairman = Hon. Arturo Agapito Orosco, Sr., Ph.D.\n| chancellor = \n| president = Arturo O\u00f1as Orosco, Jr., Ph.D.\n| vice-president = Arlen O\u00f1as Orosco, Ph.D.\n| superintendent = \n| provost = \n| vice_chancellor = \n| principal = \n| dean = \n| director = \n| head_label = \n| head = \n| academic_staff = \n| administrative_staff = \n| students = \n| undergrad = \n| postgrad = \n| doctoral = \n| city = Admiral Village, Talon III [[Las Pi\u00f1as City]]\n| province = [[Metro Manila]]\n| country = {{PHL}}\n| coor = \n| campus = Main Campus''':'''<br>Las Pi\u00f1as City<br>Satellite campuses''':'''<br>Alabang, Bacoor, Taguig, Dasmari\u00f1as, Southwoods, Sta. Rosa, SAS Las Pi\u00f1as, SAS Los Ba\u00f1os\n| free_label = Alma Mater song\n| free = [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7Jd-aeEc3Fs Saint Francis of Assisi College Hymn]<ref>{{cite web |title=SFAC Hymn |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7Jd-aeEc3Fs |website=You Tube |publisher=Saint Francis of Assisi College |accessdate=January 8, 2020}}</ref>\n| colors = Red {{color box|red}} and {{color box|white}} White\n| colours = \n| athletics = \n| sports = \n| nickname = Franciscan\n| sporting_affiliations = [[National Collegiate Athletic Association \u2013 South (Philippines)|NCAA-South]] [[Universities and Colleges of Luzon Athletic Association|UCLAA]] [[Las Pi\u00f1as Schools Athletic Association|LPSAA]]\n| mascot = SFAC Doves\n| website = [http://www.stfrancis.edu.ph www.stfrancis.edu.ph]\n| logo = \n| footnotes = \n}} \n'''Saint Francis of Assisi College''' ('''SFAC''') is a system of private, [[Catholic]]-oriented but non-sectarian [[Philippine]] educational institutions, offering complete education from pre-school up to the graduate or masteral level of education. The main campus is situated in [[Las Pi\u00f1as City]], [[Metro Manila]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stfrancis.edu.ph|title=About SFAC|last=|first=|date=|website=Saint Francis of Assisi College|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=January 8, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sports.inquirer.net/211863/bright-future-ahead-for-kai|title=Bright future ahead for Kai|last=Celis|first=Beth|website=sports.inquirer.net|language=en|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n[[File:SFAC Facade.jpg|thumb|260x260px|The SFAC Building of Main Campus]]\nThe Saint Francis of Assisi College (SFAC) is a learning institution offering education from pre-school up to the graduate level. Founded in 1981 with about 80 pre-school pupils, SFAC now consists of more than 10,000 students spread across nine campuses in the Southern Luzon area. Main Campus is located in Admiral Village, Talon III, Las Pi\u00f1as City. Saint Francis of Assisi College (SFAC) is one of the prime educational institutions with Home Study Culture in the Philippines that began in the early 1990s where the program was not yet recognized in the country.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stfrancis.edu.ph|title=About Us|last=|first=|date=|website=Saint Francis of Assisi College|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=January 8, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title=Basic Education Student Handbook|last=|first=|publisher=Saint Francis of Assisi College|year=2019|isbn=|location=|pages=1-3}}</ref>\n\n==Campuses==\n\n* SFAC Las Pi\u00f1as (Main Campus)\n* SFAC [[Bacoor]] Campus\n* SFAC [[Taguig]] Campus\n* SFAC [[Alabang]] Campus\n* SFAC [[Dasmari\u00f1as]] Campus\n* SFAC [[Southwoods]] Campus\n* SFAC [[Sta. Rosa, Laguna]] Campus\n* Saint Anthony School [[Los Ba\u00f1os, Laguna]]\n* Saint Anthony School, [[Las Pi\u00f1as City]]\n\n==Basic Education Program ==\n*[https://stfrancis.edu.ph/getting-to-know-sfacs-early-childhood-learning-program-eclp/ Preschool Program]\n**Nursery\n**Pre-Kindergarten\n**Kindergarten\n*Elementary Grades 1-6\n*Science Elementary Grades 4-6\n*High School\n**[https://stfrancis.edu.ph/curriculum/#researchenchancedJuniorhighschool Research-Enhanced Junior High School], Grade 7 - Grade 10\n**[https://homestudyph.wixsite.com/fhsp Franciscan Home Study Program]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.philstar.com/entertainment/2010/06/17/584609/rayver-graduates-college|title=Rayver graduates from college|website=philstar.com|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref>, Grade 7 - Grade 10\n**Senior High School, Grade 11 - Grade 12\n***Science & Technology, Engineering & Mathematics (STEM)\n***Accountancy, Business and Management (ABM)\n***Humanities and Social Sciences (HUMSS)\n***General Academics (GAs)\n***Technical, Vocational and Livelihood (TVL) - Home Economics (HE)\n***Technical, Vocational and Livelihood (TVL) - Information and Communications Technology (ICT)\n\n==Higher Education Program ==\n* School of Nursing\n**Bachelor of Science in Nursing (BSN) (4 years)\n* School of Computer Studies\n**Bachelor of Science in Computer Science BSCS (4 years)\n*School of Engineering\n**Bachelor of Science in Electronics and Communications Engineering BSCECE (5 years)\n**Bachelor of Science in Computer Engineering BSCoE (5 years)\n**Bachelor of Science in Electronics Engineering BSEE (5 years)\n*School of Business Administration\n**Bachelor of Science in Business Administration (BSBA) (4 years)\n**Bachelor of Science in Hotel and Restaurant Management (BSHRM) (4 years)\n*School of Education and Liberal Arts\n**Bachelor of Elementary Education (BEEd) (4 years)\n**Bachelor of Secondary Education (BSEd) (4 years)\n**Bachelor of Arts in Psychology (ABPsy) (4 years)\n*Graduate Studies\n**Master of Arts in Education - Major in Educational Management (MaEd)\n**Master of Arts in education - Major in Guidance and Counseling (MaEd)\n**Master in Business Management (MBM)\n\n\n==Notable alumni==\n[[Ranidel de Ocampo]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/list/tag/ranidel-de-ocampo|title=Topic page on ranidel-de-ocampo|website=ABS-CBN News|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> - Professional basketball player for [[Meralco Bolts]] of [[Philippine Basketball Association]] (PBA)\n\n[[Rayver Cruz]] or Raymond Oliver Cruz Ilustre<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.philstar.com/entertainment/2010/06/17/584609/rayver-graduates-college|title=Rayver graduates from college|website=philstar.com|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> - Television artist at [[ABS-CBN (TV network)|ABS-CBN]] and [[GMA Network (company)|GMA]]\n\n[[Marian Rivera|Marian Rivera - Dantes]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gmanetwork.com/entertainment/showbiznews/news/11915/marian-rivera-honored-by-high-school-alma-mater/story|title=Marian Rivera honored by high school alma mater|website=www.gmanetwork.com|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> - Television artist, endorser and model\n\n[[Sitti|Sitti Navarro]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/06/09/11/sitti-bossa-nova-no-more|title=Sitti: Bossa nova no more?|last=News|first=ABS-CBN|website=ABS-CBN News|language=en|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref> - The \"Filipino Bossa Nova\", singer and song writer\n\n[[Wesley So]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rappler.com/sports/by-sport/other-sports/244051-things-to-know-about-wesley-so-chess|title=FAST FACTS: Who is Wesley So?|l