s==\n* The [[United States presidential election debates, 2004|2004 Vice Presidential Debate]] between then-Vice President [[Dick Cheney]] and Senator [[John Edwards]] was held on Case Western campus.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/politics/debatereferee/debate_1005.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=August 25, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171021131134/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/politics/debatereferee/debate_1005.html |archive-date=October 21, 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Association of Independent Technological Universities]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite book\n|title=A History of Western Reserve College: During Its First Half Century, 1826\u20131876\n|first=Carroll\n|last=Cutler\n|location=Cleveland\n|publisher=Crocker's\n|year=1876\n|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CshMkzMMidsC}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* [http://athletics.case.edu Case Western Reserve Athletics website]\n{{Case Western Reserve University}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Links to related articles\n| state = collapsed\n| titlestyle = background:#0A304E; color:white; border:2px solid #626262\n| list1 =\n{{University Athletic Association navbox}}\n{{Association of American Universities}}\n{{Universities Research Association}}\n{{Colleges and universities in Ohio}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Case Western Reserve University| ]]\n[[Category:1826 establishments in Ohio]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1826]]\n[[Category:Technological universities in the United States]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Cleveland]]\n[[Category:University Circle]]\n[[Category:V-12 Navy College Training Program]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges formed by merger in the United States]]\n", "name_user": "Naraht", "label": "safe", "comment": "cleanup, replaced: [[North-American Interfraternity Conference| \u2192 [[North 