. Sutton led the Cowboys to two Final Four appearances during his time as coach.\n* [[National Wrestling Hall of Fame and Museum]]\n* [[Student Union (Oklahoma State University)|Student Union]] \u2013 Known as the largest [[Student activity center|student union]] in the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://union.okstate.edu/about_union.htm |title=About Us |publisher=Union.okstate.edu |date=August 20, 1950 |accessdate=February 24, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110717041139/http://union.okstate.edu/about_union.htm |archivedate=July 17, 2011 }}</ref> Portions of the 1992 film ''[[All-American Murder]]'' were filmed at the Student Union.<ref>{{cite web | title=Filming Locations for All-American Murder (1992) (V) | publisher=[[Internet Movie Database]]\n|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0103652/locations | accessdate=January 28, 2007}}</ref>\n* [[Whitehurst Hall]] administration building\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Oklahoma}}\n* [[Gift of a Lifetime]]\n* [[Johnny Bright Incident]] \u2013 An incident that occurred during a football game on Saturday, October 20, 1951\n* [[List of forestry universities and colleges]]\n{{Clear}}\n*[[Oklahoma Agricultural Experiment Station]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Oklahoma State University}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* [http://www.okstate.com/ Oklahoma State Athletics website]\n* {{Cite Collier's|wstitle=Oklahoma Agricultural and Mechanical College |short=x}}\n\n{{Oklahoma State University|campus}}\n{{Big 12 Conference navbox}}\n{{Colleges and universities in Oklahoma}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Oklahoma State University-Stillwater}}\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Stillwater, Oklahoma]]\n[[Category:Education in Payne County, Oklahoma]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1890]]\n[[Category:Land-grant universities and colleges]]\n[[Category:Oklahoma State University| ]]\n[[Category:Veterinary schools in the United States]]\n[[Category:Tourist attracti